history.content:
- If you have a course conflict during lecture time which is another class, your finals will conflict. It's up to course staff whether they want to offer you an alternate final. Don't be surprised if they don't. 

- Apply the 10% rule to determine whether you will get off the waitlist: usually, 10% of the total class enrollment will drop. If the total class size is over 750 for CS188, absent other information, you can expect to get off the waitlist

- If you don't meet the requirements for the class, ask yourself seriously whether you should be taking it. 

I would suggest dropping the class and enrolling in one of the preqs instead.

Hi, I was hoping to enroll in CS188 this coming semester. However, I got an email saying that I do not meet any requirements for the class. Also, I have a course conflict during lecture time of this class. I am currently on waitlist 75, do you think it’s worth waiting? what are my chances of getting in considering those two factors I mentioned above?
